<h1 align="center">Valid Parentheses Problem using Stack</h1>
ğŸ§  Basic Idea

We are given:

A string s containing only brackets:
(, ), {, }, [, ]

ğŸ¯ Goal:
Check whether the given string of brackets is valid.

A string is considered valid if:

Every opening bracket has a matching closing bracket

Brackets are closed in the correct order (proper nesting)

ğŸ§° Why Stack?

We need:

ğŸ“Œ To track unmatched opening brackets

ğŸ” To process brackets in Last In, First Out (LIFO) order

âœ… Stack is perfect:

Push opening brackets

Pop when a matching closing bracket appears

ğŸªœ Step-by-Step Explanation
1ï¸âƒ£ Create a Stack

We create an empty stack:

Stack<Character> st


It stores:

opening brackets â†’ '(', '{', '['

2ï¸âƒ£ Traverse the string

We loop through each character of the string using index i.

3ï¸âƒ£ Handle opening brackets

If the current character is:

'('

'{'

'['

ğŸ‘‰ Push it onto the stack.

4ï¸âƒ£ Handle closing brackets

If the current character is a closing bracket:

âŒ If the stack is empty
â†’ no matching opening bracket
â†’ return false

âŒ If the top of the stack does not match the closing bracket
â†’ invalid pair
â†’ return false

âœ… Otherwise
â†’ matching pair found
â†’ pop the top element from the stack

5ï¸âƒ£ Final check

After traversing the entire string:

âœ… If the stack is empty â†’ all brackets matched â†’ valid

âŒ If the stack is not empty â†’ unmatched opening brackets â†’ invalid

âš¡ Example Walkthrough

Input:

s = "{[()]}"

Character	Stack State	Action
{	{	push
[	{ [	push
(	{ [ (	push
)	{ [	pop
]	{	pop
}	empty	pop

ğŸ“Œ Output:

true

ğŸ§® Complexity Analysis
Metric	Complexity
Time	O(n)
Space	O(n)
ğŸ’» Code
import java.util.Stack;

class Solution {
    public boolean isValid(String s) {

        Stack<Character> st = new Stack<>();

        for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
            char c = s.charAt(i);

            // If opening bracket, push onto stack
            if (c == '(' || c == '{' || c == '[') {
                st.push(c);
            }
            // If closing bracket
            else {
                if (st.isEmpty() ||
                   (c == ')' && st.peek() != '(') ||
                   (c == '}' && st.peek() != '{') ||
                   (c == ']' && st.peek() != '[')) {
                    return false;
                }
                st.pop(); // Matching pair found
            }
        }

        // Stack should be empty if valid
        return st.isEmpty();
    }
}
